HEADWORD: Schizorhinal
<hw>Schiz`o*rhi"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Schizo-</ets> + <ets>rhinal</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the nasal bones separate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the anterior nostrils
prolonged backward in the form of a slit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Schlich</ent>⟦br⟧
